# Non-Primary Energy Ratio Discriminator

This project trains a simple Transformer regressor on mixed music clips.

Given one mixture waveform, the model predicts:

```text
non_primary_ratio = (total_stem_energy - primary_stem_energy) / total_stem_energy
```

Here, the "primary" stem is defined as the stem with the largest energy inside the current training segment.

## Dataset

By default, the code points at:

```text
../deep_sleeping/dataset generator/generated
```

Each project folder is expected to contain:

- `mixture.wav`
- `stems/*.wav`
- `metadata.json`

## Install

```powershell
cd "C:\Users\fison\Desktop\class\DL\discriminator\dis"
uv sync --python 3.11
```

## Train

```powershell
uv run dis-train --epochs 20 --batch-size 8 --segment-seconds 6
```

To override the dataset path:

```powershell
uv run dis-train --dataset-root "C:\path\to\generated"
```

## Predict

```powershell
uv run dis-predict --checkpoint .\runs\best.pt --mixture "C:\path\to\mixture.wav"
```

## AutoDL notes

On AutoDL, upload the `dis/` folder and point `--dataset-root` at the generated dataset on the server:

```bash
cd /root/autodl-tmp/dis
python -m pip install -e .
dis-train --dataset-root /root/autodl-tmp/generated --device cuda
```
